    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix null pointer dereference in multipath_tv_channel function\n\n### Summary\nThe `multipath_tv_channel` function in the OpenAirInterface simulation tools was vulnerable to null pointer dereferences when called with invalid parameters. This could lead to segmentation faults during channel simulation, particularly when processing time-varying channel models.\n\nThe issue occurred due to missing null checks on input parameters and memory allocation results. When the function was called with null pointers for channel descriptor or signal arrays, or when memory allocation failed, the code would attempt to dereference null pointers, causing crashes.\n\nThis fix adds comprehensive null pointer checks and proper error handling throughout the function and its downstream dependencies.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/TOOLS/multipath_tv_channel.c`: Added null pointer validation for all input parameters, memory allocation failure checks, and proper cleanup routines.\n"
}